<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta content='text/html; charset=UTF-8' http-equiv='Content-Type' />
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <%= @from_user.name %> has requested feedback on their <%= @badge.progress_log %> for the 
      <%= @badge.name %> badge in Badge List.
      To add your feedback log into Badge List or click one of the links below. 
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Is it your first time? Adding your feedback is easy.</strong>
      <ol>
        <li>Review their <%= @badge.progress_log %></li>
        <li>Click "Add feedback"</li>
        <li>Decide whether or not they have earned the badge</li>
        <li>Write specific feedback and notes</li>
      </ol>
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong><%= @from_user.name %>'s <%= @badge.progress_log.titleize %>:</strong> 
      <%= link_to group_badge_log_url(@group, @badge, @log), 
        group_badge_log_url(@group, @badge, @log) %> <br>
      <strong><%= @badge.name %>:</strong> 
      <%= link_to group_badge_url(@group, @badge), group_badge_url(@group, @badge) %> <br>
      <strong><%= @group.name %>:</strong> 
      <%= link_to group_url(@group), group_url(@group) %> 
    </p>
    <p>
      <i><b>
        <% if @is_badge_member %>
          To stop receiving feedback request emails for this badge 
          <%= link_to "edit your badge membership", 
            group_badge_url(@group, @badge) + '#log-visibility' %>.
        <% else %>
          You are receiving feedback request emails because you are a group admin. If you'd like to
          stop receiving feedback request emails you will need to join the badge and edit your
          badge membership to set your preferences.
        <% end %>
      </b></i>
    </p>
    <p>
      <i>
        This email was sent automatically by the Badge List app.
        Badge List is a badge-based tool for tracking learning progress. 
        If you take no action you will not receive any further emails about this change.
      </i>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>